## üèóÔ∏è Architecture Patterns

### 1. Content Management Pattern

**Projects Collection** (`_projects/`)
- Each project is a **markdown file with YAML frontmatter**
- Collection configured in `_config.yml` with `output: false` (no individual pages generated)
- Projects are rendered in `index.html` via Liquid templating

**Project Frontmatter Schema (Multi-Dimensional Taxonomy):**
```yaml
---
title: Project Name
anchor_id: unique-id                # Used for anchor navigation
card_image: images/path.png         # Thumbnail for project grid

# Multi-dimensional Taxonomy (all optional)
xr_technology: AR                   # AR, VR, MR, or XR
domain:                             # Industry domains (can be multiple)
  - Medical
  - Manufacturing
project_type:                       # Project types (can be multiple)
  - App
  - R&D
  - CV
platform: HoloLens                  # Primary platform
featured: true                      # Mark as featured project

tags: [Keywords, Additional]       # Additional keywords (optional)
summary: Short description          # Displayed on cards
external_url: https://...           # Optional link
external_label: "Link Text"         # Optional label
---
Content goes here (Markdown)
```

**Taxonomy Categories:**
- **XR Technology:** AR, VR, MR, XR (single value)
- **Industry Domain:** Medical, Manufacturing, Commercial, Education, Entertainment (can be multiple)
- **Project Type:** Game, App, R&D, CV (Computer Vision), AI (AI/ML), Tool (can be multiple)
- **Platform:** HoloLens, Quest, PCVR, Mobile, Web, Desktop, Cross-Platform (single value)
- **Featured:** Boolean flag to highlight important projects

**Blog Posts Collection** (`_posts/`)
- Standard Jekyll blog posts with date-based naming: `YYYY-MM-DD-slug.md`
- Default layout: `post` (configured in `_config.yml`)
- Default author: "Mahad Mufti"

### 2. Layout System

**Three main layouts:**

1. **`default.html`** - Base template for all pages
   - Includes: head, nav, footer, scripts
   - Dark mode toggle button
   - Wrapper structure for single-page design

2. **`project.html`** - Simple project layout
   - Minimal frontmatter requirements
   - Back button to `#work`
   - Used for projects that need custom HTML (currently not actively used)

3. **`case-study.html`** - Advanced project layout (future use)
   - Structured sections: Overview, Role, Tech Stack, Challenges, Results
   - Link management
   - Tag display
   - Currently prepared but not actively used

**Current Implementation Note:**
- Most projects are **hardcoded directly in `index.html`** as `<article>` panels
- This is a legacy pattern; new projects should consider using the layout system

### 3. Navigation Pattern

**Single-Page Anchor Navigation:**
- Home panel: `#home`
- Work/Projects grid: `#work`
- Individual projects: `#360lens`, `#hotspring`, `#sldvr`, etc.
- Each project panel includes a "Go Back" button linking to `#work`

**Panel Structure:**
```html
<article id="unique-anchor" class="panel">
  <header>
    <a href="#work" style="float: right;"><button>Go Back</button></a>
    <h2>Project Title</h2>
    <a href="external-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><u>Link Label</u></a>
  </header>
  <section>
    <!-- Project content -->
  </section>
</article>
```

### 4. Project Grid & Multi-Dimensional Filtering

**Filtering System** (Dropdown-based, in `default.html` script):
- **XR Technology Dropdown:** AR, VR, MR, XR
- **Industry Domain Dropdown:** Medical, Manufacturing, Commercial, Education, Entertainment
- **Project Type Dropdown:** Games, Applications, R&D, Computer Vision, AI/ML, Tools
- **Search Box:** Text-based filtering by title, summary, and tags
- **Reset Button:** Clears all active filters
- **Results Counter:** Shows "Showing X of Y projects"

**Multi-Dimensional Logic:**
- Projects can belong to multiple categories (domain and project_type support arrays)
- Filtering uses **AND logic** (all active filters must match)
- Projects appear when they match ALL selected criteria
- Easily manageable through Netlify CMS dropdown fields

**Grid Implementation with Data Attributes:**
```html
<div class="row aln-center" id="projects-grid">
  {% for project in site.projects %}
    <div class="col-4 project-card" 
         data-xr="{{ project.xr_technology }}"
         data-domain="{{ project.domain | join: ',' }}"
         data-type="{{ project.project_type | join: ',' }}"
         data-platform="{{ project.platform }}"
         data-featured="{{ project.featured }}"
         data-tags="{{ project.tags | join: ',' | downcase }}"
         data-title="{{ project.title | downcase }}"
         data-summary="{{ project.summary | downcase }}">
      <a href="#{{ project.anchor_id }}">
        <img src="{{ project.card_image | relative_url }}">
        {% if project.featured %}
          <span class="featured-badge">‚òÖ Featured</span>
        {% endif %}
      </a>
      <div class="project-meta">
        {% if project.xr_technology %}
          <span class="project-badge badge-xr">{{ project.xr_technology }}</span>
        {% endif %}
        {% for domain in project.domain %}
          <span class="project-badge badge-domain">{{ domain }}</span>
        {% endfor %}
      </div>
      <h2>{{ project.title }}</h2>
      <p>{{ project.summary }}</p>
    </div>
  {% endfor %}
</div>
```

**Visual Features:**
- **Category Badges:** Color-coded badges for XR technology and domains
- **Featured Badge:** Gold star badge for highlighted projects
- **Responsive Design:** Mobile-friendly dropdown layout

### 5. Theme System

**Dark Mode Implementation:**
- Toggle button in `default.html`
- Uses `data-theme` attribute on `<html>` element
- Persists preference in localStorage
- CSS custom properties in `dark-mode.css`
- Icons: üåô for light mode, ‚òÄÔ∏è for dark mode

### 6. Image Organization

**Convention:**
- Images stored in `/images/ProjectName/` folders
- Organized by project (360Lens/, Apriltag/, Dicom/, etc.)
- Referenced via Liquid relative_url filter: `{{ '/images/path.png' | relative_url }}`

**Gallery Pattern:**
```html
<div class="gallery">
  <h3 style="text-align:center; margin-bottom: 0.75em;">Gallery</h3>
  <div class="gallery-grid">
    <a href="{{ '/images/Project/image.png' | relative_url }}" data-gallery="project-name">
      <img loading="lazy" src="{{ '/images/Project/image.png' | relative_url }}" alt="Description">
    </a>
  </div>
</div>
```

### 7. Netlify CMS Integration

**Configuration** (`admin/config.yml`):
- Backend: GitHub (repo: mahadishere/portfolio)
- OAuth via Decap (Vercel-hosted)
- Collections: projects, posts, site_settings
- Media folder: `/images`

**Content Editing:**
- Non-technical users can edit via `/admin` interface
- Changes commit directly to GitHub master branch
- Automatic deployment via GitHub Pages

